---

<section class="claim-evidence">
  <h2>Claim vs Evidence</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Common claim</th>
        <th>What high-quality evidence shows</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Statins cause memory loss</td>
        <td>No excess in blinded randomized trials</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Statins cause dementia or Alzheimerâ€™s</td>
        <td>No causal association detected</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Statins cause depression</td>
        <td>No evidence of increased risk</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Statins disrupt sleep</td>
        <td>No signal in randomized data</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Statins cause sexual dysfunction</td>
        <td>No increase versus placebo</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Statins damage the kidneys</td>
        <td>No increase in AKI or renal failure</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Statins commonly injure the liver</td>
        <td>Mild lab abnormalities only; serious injury rare</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Statins cause muscle pain in many patients</td>
        <td>Small real increase, mostly early in treatment</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Statins frequently cause diabetes</td>
        <td>Modest, dose-dependent risk in predisposed patients</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>
